world.bentobox.bentobox.blueprints

Class BlueprintClipboard

  • java.lang.Object
    • world.bentobox.bentobox.blueprints.BlueprintClipboard

  • public class BlueprintClipboard
extends Object
    The clipboard provides the holding spot for an active blueprint that is being manipulated by a user. It supports copying from the world and setting of coordinates such as the bounding box around the cuboid copy area. Pasting is done by the BlueprintPaster class.
    Since:
    1.5.0
    Author:
    tastybento

      • copy

        public boolean copy(User user,
                    boolean copyAir)
        Copy the blocks between pos1 and pos2 into the clipboard for a user. This will erase any previously registered data from the clipboard. Copying is done async.
        Parameters:
        user - - user
        Returns:
        true if successful, false if pos1 or pos2 are undefined.
